PRIVACY POLICY
LAST UPDATED: JANUARY 25, 2024
Daily Yoga Software Technology Co. Ltd. ("
DailyYoga.com
") provides this Privacy Policy to demonstrate
DailyYoga.com
's firm commitment to your privacy and privacy-related concerns. This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time for any reason; each version will apply to information collected while it was in place. From time to time updates and modifications may be made available on
DailyYoga.com
and you are advised to consult this Privacy Policy regularly for any changes.
The following sets forth
DailyYoga.com
's information gathering, use, and dissemination practices. If you have any questions or comments about this Privacy Policy or our use of your personally identifiable information, please contact us at Support@DailyYoga.com.
DailyYoga.com
does not collect personal information -- names, addresses, phone numbers, e-mail addresses, and specific locations -- about you except when you specifically provide such information voluntarily; for example, when you provide
DailyYoga.com
with information in connection with a website registration.
A Special Note About Children.
Children are not eligible to use our services and we ask that minors do not submit any personal information to us. If you are a minor, you can use this service only in conjunction with your parents or guardians. If we become aware that a child under 13 has provided us with personally identifiable Information, we will delete such information from our files. We use your email address and, in rare situations, your mailing address or phone number, to contact you regarding administrative notices from time to time.
Information Collection and Use
As a valued visitor to
DailyYoga.com
, we will occasionally contact you, typically by e-mail (or any other way you prefer) to notify you of special promotions, and up-to-date news, custom-tailored to your interests. Of course, if you do not wish to receive this personalized information, you can always let us know by emailing us at support@dailyyoga.com, and we will happily abide by your wishes.
DailyYoga.com
uses your Internet Protocol (IP) address to help diagnose problems with our computer server and to administer our website. Your IP address is used to help identify you and to gather broad demographic data. Your IP address contains no personal information about you.
To ensure that all of your personal information is correct and up-to-date, at any time you may visit your profile via our yoga coaching application ‘Daily Yoga’. Through your profile, you may: (a) review and update your personal information that
DailyYoga.com
has already collected; (b) choose whether or not you wish us to share some of your Personal Information in Daily Yoga’s community.
Users of this website must promptly notify
DailyYoga.com
if personally identifiable information is lost, stolen, or used without permission. In such an event, we can help you reset your password, hold or cancel your account, and update our records accordingly.
Daily Yoga will require permission to access your camera which is used to take photos when you voluntarily share your photos in the Daily Yoga Community. And please make sure you have the right to share these pictures before sharing.
Location permission is required for geotagging of your posts. If enabled, your location will be shown to others when you make a post in the Daily Yoga Community.
Daily Yoga requires permission to read your Phone State, such as Device ID to bind your device with your Daily Yoga Account and Network Type to help avoid unnecessary data consumption.
To request the deletion of your personal data that we have in the Daily Yoga App, please find the "Delete Account" in the Profile Settings. Or you can email us at support@dailyyoga.com to request the deletion, and we will respond to your request in a reasonable timeframe. Upon your request, Daily Yoga will permanently and irrevocably anonymize your data such that it can never be reconstructed to identify you as an individual.
When you participate in the active rankings, Daily Yoga will use your IP address to obtain country and region information. Your IP address contains no personal information about you. You can still reset your region information on the Profile page.
Data Protection
Protecting users' personal information is our top priority. To ensure the security of sensitive data, we have implemented the following measures:
- Data Encryption:
We use advanced encryption technology to secure the transmission and storage of sensitive data.
- Access Control:
Only authorized personnel can access sensitive data due to strict access control measures.
- Secure Data Storage:
Sensitive data is stored in secure servers and protected environments to prevent unauthorized access.
We collect data to enhance the functionality of the application, improve user experience, customize features, and optimize performance. Our data collection practices comply with applicable data protection laws and regulations.
Cookies
We use "cookie" technology to collect non-personal website usage data and to improve the Site and our service. Cookies are files a website can use to recognize repeat users, and allow a website to track web usage behavior. Cookies take up minimal room on your computer and cannot damage your computer’s files. Daily Yoga Software Technology Co. Ltd. may use both session cookies and persistent cookies to better understand how you interact with the
DailyYoga.com
website and services, monitor aggregate usage by our users and web traffic routing on the website, and improve the website and our services. A session cookie enables certain features of the site and our service and is deleted from your computer when you disconnect from or leave
DailyYoga.com
. A persistent cookie remains after you close your browser and may be used by your browser on subsequent visits to
DailyYoga.com
. Persistent cookies can be removed by following your web browser's help file directions. Most Internet browsers automatically accept cookies. You can instruct your browser, by editing its options, to stop accepting cookies or to prompt you before accepting a cookie from the websites you visit.
Information Sharing Disclosure
DailyYoga.com
does not sell or rent personal information about its customers to any third parties at this time. In the event
DailyYoga.com
does engage in such commerce in the future, you will have an opportunity to remove yourself from any such lists before your inclusion therein by emailing us at unsubscribe@DailyYoga.com. Please exercise caution when deciding to disclose your personal information. This website also contains links to other websites.
DailyYoga.com
is not responsible for the privacy practices or the content of such websites.
DailyYoga.com
uses third-party advertising companies to serve ads and the third-party advertising companies may use non-personally identifiable information about a user’s visits to
DailyYoga.com
to provide advertisements about goods and services that may be of interest to users. Users of
DailyYoga.com
can find more information about these practices and their choices concerning these practices at
http://networkadvertising.org/managing/opt_out.asp
.
GoogleFit
As a fitness-related application, we support your connection to GoogleFit in order to provide you with more comprehensive services. You can choose whether to use GoogleFit based on your personal preferences. Additionally, we would like to inform you that DailyYoga's use and transfer of information received from Google APIs will adhere to
Google API Services User Data Policy
, including the requirements for limited use.
Compliance with Laws and Law Enforcement
DailyYoga.com
cooperates with all law enforcement inquiries and with all third parties to enforce their intellectual property or other rights. We may disclose any information about you to government or law enforcement officials or private parties as we, in our sole discretion, believe necessary or appropriate to respond to claims, and legal processes (including subpoenas), to protect the property and rights of Daily Yoga Software Technology Co. Ltd. or a third party, the safety of the public or any person, to prevent or stop any illegal, unethical, or legally actionable activity, or to comply with the law.
DailyYoga.com
takes your privacy concerns very seriously. If you still have concerns about privacy issues after reading this Privacy Policy, please contact us at Support@DailyYoga.com. This Privacy Policy is effective as of May 1, 2011. This Privacy Policy is not intended to and does not create any contractual or other legal rights in or on behalf of any party. We reserve the right, at any time and without notice, to add to, change, update, or modify this Privacy Policy, simply by posting such change, update, or modification on the Site. Any such change, update, or modification will be effective immediately upon posting on the Site.